The paper deals with supervised learning algorithms and their scalability to large datasets, which is a common topic in machine learning and data science. The use of ensemble learning and novel techniques for scalability also suggests a focus on machine learning. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) are the most likely sub-categories. The use of Big Data frameworks and distributed computing also suggests a focus on databases and data management, making cs.DB (Databases) a likely sub-category as well. The paper also deals with classification and decision making, which are common topics in artificial intelligence, making cs.AI a possible sub-category. Finally, the use of Gini impurity in the pruning phase suggests a focus on data mining, making cs.DM (Data Mining) a possible sub-category.
